<headline>Winter Weather Advisory issued December 27 at 8:57PM MST until December 28 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Pocatello</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 AM MST
TUESDAY...
* WHAT...Additional accumulations of 1 to 3 inches. Wind gusts
up to 35 mph will create some blowing and drifting snow.
* WHERE...Centennial and Big Hole Mountains including Targhee
and Pine Creek Passes. Portions of U S Route 20 and State
Highway 87.
* WHEN...Until 5 AM MST Tuesday.
* IMPACTS...Travel may remain difficult to impossible at times.
Blowing and drifting snow will significantly reduce visibility
and drifting snow create temporary road closures.</description>
<instruction>Slow down and use caution while traveling.
The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.</instruction>
